  "prompt": "How does a selfie stick works with an Android phone?",
  "response": "A selfie stick works with an Android phone through these basic steps:\n\n1. Connection Methods:\n- Bluetooth connection\n- Wired connection via 3.5mm audio jack\n- USB connection\n- Wireless remote control\n\n2. Bluetooth Selfie Stick:\n- Pair the selfie stick with your Android phone via Bluetooth\n- Press the shutter button on the stick to take photos\n- Requires Bluetooth to be enabled on your phone\n- Works within a certain range (typically 30-50 feet)\n\n3. Wired Connection:\n- Plug the stick's cable into your phone's headphone or USB port\n- Use the built-in button to trigger the camera shutter\n- No battery or pairing required\n- Compatible with most Android phones\n\n4. Features:\n- Extendable pole for various angles\n- Adjustable phone mount\n- Lightweight and portable\n- Some models include built-in tripods\n\n5. Camera App Compatibility:\n- Works with most default camera apps\n- Compatible with third-party camera apps\n- Some advanced sticks require specific apps\n\n6. Additional Tips:\n- Check Bluetooth/wired compatibility before purchasing\n- Ensure your phone's operating system supports the stick\n- Verify mount size matches your phone's dimensions",
